<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Ten days ago OpenAI was worth $86 billion. Inv=
estors in OpenAI were about to launch a tender offer to buy employee shares=
 at that valuation, and employees were lining up to tender; there were will=
ing buyers and sellers at that price. Then events occurred. There was a boa=
rdroom coup, and OpenAI=E2=80=99s founder and chief executive officer, Sam =
Altman, was fired. At one point, the valuation of OpenAI was apparently=C2=
=A0<em>zero dollars:=C2=A0</em>Several OpenAI investors were noisily saying=
 that they were going to <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com=
/click/33498739.286429/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVz=
