kground-color: #ccc;">Alan James Kluegel</a> emailed me to suggest a=C2=A0t=
heory that maps the OpenAI conflict =E2=80=94=C2=A0between its nonprofit bo=
ard that worried=C2=A0about AI safety, and its employees who love Altman an=
d wanted him back =E2=80=94=C2=A0onto a straightforward valuation dispute:<=
/p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The board is made up of AI evangelists; the re=
ason they openly worry about AI getting <em>too powerful</em> is out of a b=
elief in the potential for a godlike AI or at least out of concern that thi=
s soon-to-be-ubiquitous technology should be in its best possible shape bef=
ore being distributed to the world. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The employees, however, are familiar with all =
of the AI=E2=80=99s limitations and problems and costs, and =E2=80=94 being=
 Silicon Valley veterans =E2=80=94 are also familiar with the hype cycle at=
 play here. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In other words, this is a story about the empl=
oyees wanting to secure the bag while the unrealized potential of their pro=
duct has captured everyone=E2=80=99s attention and imagination, and Sam Alt=
man=E2=80=99s fundraising (and the Thrive Capital tender offer, in particul=
ar) was going to be their golden ticket =E2=80=94=C2=A0until the starry-eye=
d board killed their payday in a flurry of techno-optimistic excitement.</p=
>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This is absolutely not at all what anyone was=
=C2=A0<em>saying</em>, and I suspect that it is not what anyone was=C2=A0<e=
m>thinking</em>, but I like it as an objective explanation of what they wer=
e=C2=A0<em>doing</em>. It is not unheard-of=C2=A0for a startup to get a pre=
tty high valuation, and for its employees to think =E2=80=9Chey let=E2=80=
=99s cash out while the money is there,=E2=80=9D while its board members ar=
e venture capitalists with diversified portfolios and liquidation preferenc=
es who are more willing to wait and gamble. Venture capitalist board member=
s are=C2=A0<em>supposed=C2=A0</em>to be able to take the long view and bet =
on changing the world, while employees are often more risk-averse and need =
cash to pay the mortgage.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-3" s=
tyle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wid=
th: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important=
; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
