<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here are two possible=C2=A0theories of what Bi=
nance=C2=A0<em>is:</em></p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Binance is the world=E2=80=99s leadin=
g crypto exchange, a large financial institution that allows investors, spe=
culators, hedgers and other users to transact in the trillion-dollar crypto=
currency sector. It is in many ways the leading financial institution in cr=
ypto, but it is fairly young and aggressive, and it has not always been ver=
y careful about compliance. In particular, it has not been careful about an=
ti-money-laundering and know-your-customer checks, and so has allowed a cer=
tain number of bad people to do bad transactions using crypto.</li>=09<li s=
tyle=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Binance is a place for laundering money.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">These theories differ in degree; they start fr=
om similar facts but emphasize them differently. Nobody disputes that a lot=
