ively sanctioned jurisdictions, but it did not implement sufficiently effec=
tive controls to prevent such sanctions violations from occurring. For exam=
ple, Defendant could have removed from Binance=E2=80=99s platform all accou=
nts associated with either (i) U.S. users or (ii) users in comprehensively =
sanctioned jurisdictions. Or Defendant could have implemented controls in i=
ts matching engine to prevent U.S. users from violating sanctions by preven=
ting them from transacting with users in comprehensively sanctioned jurisdi=
ctions.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">What an amazing suggestion. The Justice Depart=
